                <note rend="inline" type="source">367.1164 Brusa School Trial/20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-17T10:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1928—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 17—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. For Shaw: No doubt you will have considered domestic editorial value of press
                    statement from Lansing, Michigan, that Attorney General of Michigan has handed
                    down opinion that religious instruction in public schools of that state is
                    unconstitutional because separation of church and state is fundamental policy.
                    Brusa incident appears analogous.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
